name: Mike Johnson
summary: House Speaker Mike Johnson faces backlash from some right-wing Republicans for supporting foreign aid to Ukraine. Despite this, he has declared that he will not resign and will continue to advocate for aid to both Ukraine and Israel. Johnson's approach to passing aid is being described by some as complicated and challenging. The situation has also led to a motion to oust Johnson from his position as Speaker, with a second Republican backing the effort. Johnson's decision to push for foreign aid is seen by some as a risky move that could ultimately determine his political future. The situation remains fluid, with Johnson and his opponents actively campaigning for support within the Republican Party.

Opening statements in the historic trial are scheduled to begin on Monday following a tense jury selection process. name: Coban Porter
summary: Coban Porter, the brother of Denver Nuggets star Michael Porter Jr., has been sentenced to six years in prison for his role in a fatal DUI crash. The crash occurred in 2021 and claimed the life of a 14-year-old girl. Porter, who was intoxicated at the time of the crash, pleaded guilty to vehicular homicide and other charges. The sentencing comes just days after another brother, Jontay, was banned from the NBA for gambling.

name: Stevie Nicks
summary: Stevie Nicks, known for her iconic music, has penned a moving poem for Taylor Swift's latest album, "The Tortured Poets Department." The poem, titled "For T and Me," expresses Nicks' admiration for Swift's artistry and offers a heartfelt reflection on their shared experiences of heartbreak. The poem serves as both a prologue and epilogue to the album and adds a poignant touch to the collection of songs written by Swift about the complexities of love and loss. The collaboration between the two musicians showcases their mutual understanding of the emotional depth and transformative power of music, particularly in times of vulnerability and heartbreak.
